      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): sync infer capability inspect metadata flags with registered options",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`infer inspect --name <id> --json` reports each capability's supported flags from a hand-maintained `CAPABILITY_METADATA` array in `src/cli/capability-cli.ts`. Four entries' `flags` arrays had drifted out of sync with the commands' actually-registered options, so `inspect` reported working flags as **unsupported**:\n\n| capability | registered but missing from inspect metadata |\n|---|---|\n| `model.run` | `--thinking` (registered at `capability-cli.ts:2147`) |\n| `model.auth.login` | `--method` (`:2221`) |\n| `model.auth.logout` | `--agent` (`:2239`) |\n| `audio.transcribe` | `--language` (`:2427`), `--prompt` (`:2428`) |\n\nThe flags work end-to-end (the commands register and honor them) — only the inspect inventory under-reported them, so a user or tool inspecting capabilities wouldn't discover them. The existing tests assert exact `flags` arrays for `image.edit`/`image.generate` but these four ids were unguarded.\n\nThis syncs the four arrays to the registered options (in registration order) and adds a **global invariant test** that asserts, for *every* capability id, that its metadata `flags` equal its command's registered long options — closing the drift for good.\n\n### Changes\n- `src/cli/capability-cli.ts` — add the missing flags to the 4 `CAPABILITY_METADATA` entries; `export` the array so the test can import it.\n- `src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts` — new test \"keeps capability inspect metadata flags in sync with each command's registered options\": registers the CLI and deep-equals each entry's `flags` against the registered long options walked via `id.split(\".\")`.\n\nVerified completeness: of all 31 capability ids, only these 4 drifted (every other id — `tts.*`, `video.*`, `web.*`, `embedding.*`, `image.*`, all `.providers` — already matched).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `infer inspect` under-reported the supported flags for 4 capabilities (`--thinking`/`--method`/`--agent`/`--language`/`--prompt`), so working options appeared unsupported in the inspect contract. The metadata now lists exactly what each command registers.\n\nReal environment tested: Node 22.22.1, macOS, no model / network / device. A `./node_modules/.bin/tsx` harness imports the real `CAPABILITY_METADATA` and `registerCapabilityCli`, registers the CLI, and for each of the 4 ids compares the inspect metadata flags to the command's registered long options. BEFORE is `origin/main`'s metadata (export added in for the harness only).\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```bash\n# harness: real CAPABILITY_METADATA vs registerCapabilityCli registered options\n./node_modules/.bin/tsx cap-proof.mts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```\nBEFORE (origin/main):\n  model.run: MATCH=false (inspect omits [\"--thinking\"])\n  audio.transcribe: MATCH=false (inspect omits [\"--language\",\"--prompt\"])\n  model.auth.login: MATCH=false (inspect omits [\"--method\"])\n  model.auth.logout: MATCH=false (inspect omits [\"--agent\"])\nAFTER (this branch):\n  model.run: MATCH=true\n  audio.transcribe: MATCH=true\n  model.auth.login: MATCH=true\n  model.auth.logout: MATCH=true\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: each of the 4 capabilities' inspect metadata now equals its command's registered options; on `origin/main` each omitted the flags shown above. Clean-slug commands and all other ids were already in sync and are unchanged.\n\nWhat was not tested: a full `openclaw infer inspect` run against a built CLI (the harness drives the real `registerCapabilityCli` command tree + `CAPABILITY_METADATA` directly, which is what `inspect` reads). The new global invariant test in `capability-cli.test.ts` fails before this change (the drift) and passes after, guarding the contract for every capability going forward.\n\n## Additional checks\n- `pnpm test src/cli/capability-cli.test.ts` — 98 pass (incl. the new invariant test). Verified fail-before by reverting the 4 metadata arrays → the invariant test fails with the exact drift.\n- Formatter (`oxfmt`), static analysis (`oxlint`), and `tsgo:core` pass for the changed files.\n- Completeness: the invariant test iterates all 31 capability ids, so its green run is positive proof no other id drifts.\n",
        "branch": "fix/cli-capability-metadata-flag-drift",
